	}
      ]
     ,"INC-SPECT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The HIgS facility uses a relativistic electron"
		,"storage ring and free-electron laser to produce"
		,"quasimonoenergetic gamma beams, ranging between 1-100"
		,"MeV, via laser Compton backscattering (LCB), with beam"
		,"intensities up to 3*10**10 gamma/s."]
	}
      ]
     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"SI", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Silicon detector"}
	    ,{"code":"FISCH", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Fission chamber"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The Oak Ridge National Laboratory SIDAR"
		," (SIlicon Detector ARray). Six YY1 detectors fit"
		,"together on a custom mount to form a \"lampshade\", to"
		,"maximize angular coverage at a given distance. Two"
		,"such lampshades, facing each other around the target"
		,"position, were mounted. Within each position of the"
		,"lampshade array, two detectors were mounted such that"
		,"a thin dE detector (either 65 or microm thickness)"
		,"was backed by a thick E detector (100 microm"
		,"thickness). A small fission chamber was installed"
		,"downstream of the target chamber, to measure the"
		,"gamma beam intensity via the well-known cross section"
		,"of gamma-induced fission on 238U."]
	}
      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The target material was provided by the Center for"
		,"Accelerator Target Science (CATS) at Argonne National"
		,"Laboratory. A natural, self-supporting metal zinc"
		,"foil of 1.09 mg/cm2, roughly 2 cm square, was mounted"
		,"on a thin aluminum frame at the center position of"
		,"SIDAR."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"EDE", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Particle identification by `E/Delta E` measurement"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" Two complementary techniques were used to"
		,"identify the reactions of interest in the data."
		,"Protons and alpha particles with sufficient energy"
		,"from the reaction traveled through the front dE"
		,"detector and stopped in the E detector, depositing"
		,"some energy in each, such that standard energy loss"
		,"techniques could be used for particle identification."
		,"For lower-energy charged particles that stopped in"
		,"the dE detector, a separate spectrum was produced"
		,"using the E detector as an active veto. In this"
		,"technique, the known reaction kinematics were used to"
		,"identify the region of interest for each reaction"
		,"ejectile. For each incident gamma beam energy, the"
		,"total number of proton or alpha events for each of"
		,"these techniques was summed to determine raw yields."
		,"Converting these yields to cross sections was"
		,"accomplished using the measured Zn target thickness,"
		,"detection efficiency, and gamma beam intensity as"
		,"determined from the downstream fission chamber."
		,"Natural zinc contains five stable isotopes: 64Zn,"
		,"66Zn, 67Zn, 68Zn, and 70Zn. Because of this, the"
		,"contributions to the cross section from each isotope"
		,"could not be extracted in the current work. Instead,"
		,"the total cross sections for reactions on a natural"
		,"abundance zinc target are reported."]
	}
      ]
     ,"ERR-ANALYS":[
